    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72113/425</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Alien
                        Property Custodian</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PAM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have your letter of December 22,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d358fn1">Not printed.</note> asking whether this Department sees any
                    impropriety in demands being made by the Alien Property Custodian for property
                    in this country belonging to German, Austro-Hungarian, Bulgarian and Turkish
                    consuls.</p>
                <p>In reply I hasten to let you know that this Department deems it unwise for the
                    Alien Property Custodian to make demands for property in this country belonging
                    to persons who while in this country were official representatives of a foreign
                    government.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
